{
  "texts": [
    "Addressing UHI nowcasting specifically, [139] put forth a promising online system for nowcasting satellite-derived temperatures in major cities.",
    "This system aims to facilitate real-time forecasting of UHI as well as timely predictions of energy demand and the potential impact on human health.Collaborative efforts among researchers, urban planners, and data scientists are essential for the successful implementation of data-driven UHI mitigation strategies [140].",
    "Big Data presents a transformative opportunity in the mitigation of UHI and enables more comprehensive monitoring as well as informed decision-making [141], contributing to more sustainable and resilient urban environments.2) Earth's climate simulations and solar forcing models: The Earth climate is determined by the energy that enters and leaves the Earth's system at the top of the atmosphere (ToA).",
    "Natural and anthropogenic forcing mechanisms influence this ToA radiative balance.",
    "While e.g., solar variability and volcanic eruptions are natural drivers, the emission of greenhouse gases from fossil fuel burning and change of land use, amongst others, are man-made [142]."
  ]
}